-- Democrats, Republicans closer on budget: aide
-- 
-- Wed Apr 6, 2011 11:13am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/04/06/us-usa-budget-closer-idUSTRE73548Y20110406

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Democrats and Republicans are closer to agreement on a record spending-cut package that would keep the government running beyond a Friday deadline, a Democratic aide said on Wednesday. 

 The two sides still must agree to the overall size and composition of the package, the aide said. (Reporting by  Andy Sullivan ; Editing by  Sandra Maler )